public class PbfFileMetadataAnnotator extends com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.repeaters.BaseRepeater
Reads and writes PBF file metadata. The read() method reads the given file to determine as much metadata as possible. The write(Metadata) method adds metadata to the file if it does not contain metadata already or replaces existing metadata if it does.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)

  • Method Details

    • read

      public Metadata read()
      Reads the entire file to determine the number of ways, nodes and relations as well as the bounding rectangle of the data. Other metadata such as the build time and size are included, but since the descriptor and precision cannot be determined by reading the file they are not returned.
      Returns:
      The partial metadata (without the descriptor or data precision) determined by reading the file

    • write

      public boolean write​(Metadata metadata)
      Adds or replaces any metadata in the file with the given metadata
      Parameters:
      metadata - The metadata to add to the file or which should replace any existing metadata
      Returns:
      True if the given metadata was successfully added or if it successfully replaced existing metadata
